Steven Paul Lawrence - Chief Merchandising Officer
So, we relaunched home in third quarter and we spoke a lot about that in third quarter and how proud we were of the results. We stubbed our toe a little bit in the fourth quarter. We probably didn't have enough giftable merchandise going forward and a lot of the assortment was focused on more day-in, day-out purchases. Pleased to tell you, as we already mentioned, home was one of our strong businesses in the quarter.
So, we see that drafting into second quarter. What we've really been focusing on quite honestly for the back half of the year is really ratcheting up our gift offering within the home assortments that we can capitalize on holiday. And so, it's a little premature at this point to kind of reveal what we're doing there, but we feel like we've got some really good solutions in terms of giftable merchandise for fourth quarter.
Pamela Quintiliano - SunTrust Robinson Humphrey
And they're back to looking for the everyday products for 1Q and you have the appropriate inventory for them?
Steven Paul Lawrence - Chief Merchandising Officer
Yeah, absolutely. And I think, Michael even called out we're so happy with the home business that we have rolled out our expanded home concept or are rolling it out right now to an additional 45 doors. So, that'll get us into about 100 doors that have kind of the larger mega-sized footprint in home for us.
