Bob S. Drbul - Nomura Securities International, Inc.
Got it. Okay. And then just on the e-commerce side, how much of your offering is now online? And can you just talk a little bit about sort of fulfillment and delivery in terms of what you're achieving and improvements that you expect from the new SVP that you hired?
Steven Paul Lawrence - Chief Merchandising Officer
Sure. So, we're at a point right now where virtually 100% of our store assortment is available online. We have been ramping up, obviously, the exclusive piece of the assortment to offer an expanded assortment online with the idea being most of our stores are around 18,000 square feet on average. What if we had a 200,000-square-foot store, what would that look like? And that's kind of the guiding principle the teams are using as they're constructing assortments going forward. From a fulfillment perspective, we continue to invest in moving some goods to the distribution center to increase our fulfillment from the D.C. We're north of 40% for first quarter, so we're climbing with our goal to get into that 70% to 80% range as we get closer to holiday. We're right on track to do that.
In terms of our new head of e-commerce, really excited to have Mike aboard. He brings a lot of deep knowledge in this category. And it's premature to say exactly what all the changes he's going to bring about are. He's only been on the job about two weeks, but he's been here digging in, really getting to know the team, understand the strategy. And probably in the next call, we'll be able to give you a little more color in terms of some of the impacts he's had on the business. But I could tell you he's come in and really hit the ground running, and everybody's excited to have him here.
Michael L. Glazer - President, Chief Executive Officer & Director
Hey, Bob. It's Michael. That was a good try trying to get us to talk about the second quarter.
Bob S. Drbul - Nomura Securities International, Inc.
