Steven Paul Lawrence - Chief Merchandising Officer
So from an exposure perspective, we're not exposed on denim. We obviously shifted a chunk of the buy-in to the active athletic bottoms and that continues to do very well as Michael alluded to. He's also correct in telling you, we haven't really seen a pickup in first quarter in denim. All the vendors are telling us that they're seeing it out there amongst other accounts. And for us, long denim becomes a lot less important in the second quarter than maybe it does for other people. But what we have done is in the denim-centric categories particularly the back-to-school categories taking a good stand in denim, young men's, juniors, kids. So, we're going to be in good shape in denim heading into back-to-school and we'll be positioned to take advantage of a resurgent denim business should it happen.

