Charles P. Grom - Sterne Agee CRT
Okay. And then, just on some of the sales drivers and I think the one that's got everybody excited is the 100 new stores that you're going to touch this year. Can you just delve into what that includes, what you think the comp lift could be? And again, just remind us the timing of that when those will be completed.
Steven Paul Lawrence - Chief Merchandising Officer
Sure. This is Steve. I'll take a shot at answering that. Not to be evasive, it's hard to assign a comp number. What we've done is we went out, did a ton of research with customers and got their feedback in terms of what they wanted or were looking for from a friendly-shopping environment. We came up with a list of 12 different factors, as Michael kind of listed off some of them. It could be lighting, it could be tiles, it could be carpeting, could be new fixtures, could be mannequins, could be fitting rooms. And we've gone through and triaged our stores and said, okay, within some of these stores, what needs to be done.
In some cases, it maybe only one or two of those items. So, for example, you've been in our Meyerland store. That store was pretty close to being where we'd like it to be. We needed to do a little work on lighting and fitting rooms. In that case, we're probably not going to see a huge comp lift off of just changing the lighting a little bit or updating the fitting rooms, although it's something we needed to do so we can live up to our customers' expectation.
Other stores we're doing more comprehensive remods, and we're touching maybe 9 or 10 of those factors, we're going to see a bigger lift off of, and we feel like they're going to give us a real tailwind. So, it's hard to give you a total because there are so moving parts on a store-to-store basis that it's impossible to assign a comp to what the impact of that is going to be. In terms of timing, we're getting a handful of those stores done right now. As Michael said, we'll have even more stores done as we get into third quarter. We should be done as we get out of third quarter heading into fourth quarter and that's where we're going to see our biggest impact from new stores.
Michael L. Glazer - President, Chief Executive Officer & Director
Clearly the lift, Chuck, will come in the fourth quarter. I mean we're up against as you know a pretty difficult fourth quarter from a sales standpoint and I think that's where we'll see the results of the refixturing if you will.
Charles P. Grom - Sterne Agee CRT

